         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">25/3/87 ¶  ¶ It affords me particular pleasure, dear Sir Richard, to introduce to you the celebrated geographic traveller, the Hon. John Forrest, Minister of the Lands &amp; Surveyor General of the great ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.03.25</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Richard Owen</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MSS 1045A, Dibner manuscript collection, Smithsonian Institution Libraries, Washington, DC.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation in an unknown hand: 'to introduce Mr &amp; Mrs John Forrest'.</p>
               </note>25/3/87</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It affords me particular pleasure, dear Sir Richard, to introduce to you the celebrated geographic traveller, the Hon. John Forrest, Minister of the Lands &amp; Surveyor General of the great Crown territory of W.A. — and you will be all the more interested in him when I say that he is a native colonist of W.A.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>He could doubtless aid in tracing the remains of Diprotodon and others of the Giant Animals of former geologic epochs, so lucidly described by you, over the wide area, the surveys of which are under his supreme surveillance.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir Rich. Owen</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">K.C.B., FRS. &amp;c<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS address on back of folded folio.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
